Parliament, Thursday, 12 April 2018 – The Select Committee on Petitions and Executive Undertakings will today pay an unannounced visit to the Khayelitsha District Hospital (KDH). The visit follows a petition received from Ms Nobunto Fuzane directing complaints against the KDH staff for negligence, and findings in relation to the submissions made during hearings that there has been poor and incomplete record keeping from the KDH staff. Details of the visit is as follows: Date: Thursday, 12 April 2018 Time: 9.45 am Venue: Cnr Walter Sisulu & Steve Biko Road, Khayelitsha, Cape Town, ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE SELECT COMMITTEE ON PETITIONS AND EXECUTIVE UNDERTAKINGS, MR DUMISANE XIMBI For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Felicia Lombard
